SIMPLE: pernicious
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pernicious
<hw>Per*ni"cious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pernix</ets>, <ets>-icis</ets>.]</ety> <def>Quick; swift (to
burn).</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pernicious</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pernicious
<hw>Per*ni"cious</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>perniciosus</ets>,
from <ets>pernicies</ets> destruction, from <ets>pernecare</ets> to kill
or slay outright; <ets>per + necare</ets> to kill, slay: cf. F.
<ets>pernicieux</ets>. Cf. <er>Nuisance</er>,
<er>Necromancy</er>.]</ety> <def>Having the quality of injuring or
killing; destructive; very mischievous; baleful; malicious;
wicked.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let this <qex>pernicious</qex> hour⟦br⟧
Stand aye accursed in the calendar.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Pernicious</qex> to his health.</q>
<rj><qau>Prescott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Destructive; ruinous; deadly; noxious; injurious;
baneful; deleterious; hurtful; mischievous.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Per*ni"cious*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos>, --
<wf>Per*ni"cious*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pernicity</ent>⟦br⟧
